    "Athens has benefited from a structural supply deficit. Construction activity collapsed during the 2010–2018 austerity period, and new-build supply has been slow to recover. Meanwhile, demand — driven by tourism, expat influx, and Golden Visa buyers — has outpaced supply. The result: vacancy rates in prime areas below 3%, nightly Airbnb rates climbing 10–15% annually, and long-term rent growth averaging 8% per year in central districts.": "雅典受益于结构性供应赤字。 2010年至2018年的紧缩时期，建筑活动大幅下滑，新建建筑供应恢复缓慢。与此同时，在旅游业、外籍人士涌入和Golden Visa买家的推动下，需求已经超过了供应。结果是：黄金地段的空置率低于 3%，每晚 Airbnb 的空置率每年攀升 10-15%，而中心区的长期租金平均每年增长 8%。",
    "Athens itself has undergone a quiet renaissance. Neighbourhoods like Koukaki, Monastiraki, and Exarchia now host boutique hotels, startup offices, and a creative class that has made Greece's capital one of Europe's most exciting cities. The same cultural tailwind drives property values upward every year.": "雅典本身经历了一场安静的复兴。 Koukaki、Monastiraki 和 Exarchia 等社区现在开设了精品酒店、创业办公室和创意班，使希腊首都成为欧洲最令人兴奋的城市之一。同样的文化顺风推动房地产价值每年上涨。",
