    "Greece for the": "希腊为",
    "Greece is among Europe's most generous programs for family coverage.": "希腊是欧洲最慷慨的家庭保险计划之一。",
    "Greece is in Europe. It is a NATO member state, protected by Article 5 of the NATO charter. It is an EU member state, protected by EU institutional law, the European Court of Justice, and the full weight of European economic integration. In 30 years of MENA instability — Gulf War, Arab Spring, Syria, Yemen, Gaza — Athens has remained stable, open, and prosperous relative to regional alternatives.": "希腊位于欧洲。它是 NATO 成员国，受 NATO 宪章第 5 条保护。它是EU成员国，受到EU制度法、欧洲法院和欧洲经济一体化的全面保护。在 30 年的 MENA 不稳定时期——海湾战争、阿拉伯之春、叙利亚、也门、加沙——相对于区域替代方案，雅典一直保持稳定、开放和繁荣。",
    "Greece moved in the opposite direction. The program has remained consistently investor-friendly since its launch in 2013. The 2023 amendment — raising the threshold to €800,000 in Athens, Thessaloniki, Mykonos, and Santorini — actually benefited investors: it reduced speculative demand in premium zones while keeping the €250,000 option available across 95%+ of the country's geography, including attractive coastal markets like Piraeus, Glyfada, and the Athenian Riviera.": "希腊则朝相反的方向发展。该计划自 2013 年启动以来一直对投资者保持友好。2023 年修正案——将雅典、塞萨洛尼基、米科诺斯岛和圣托里尼的门槛提高到 80 万欧元——实际上让投资者受益：它减少了优质地区的投机需求，同时在该国 95%+ 地区保留了 25 万欧元的选择权，包括比雷埃夫斯、格利法达和圣托里尼等有吸引力的沿海市场。雅典里维埃拉。",
    "Greece operates a tiered investment system introduced in 2023–2024. The threshold depends on the property's location and type.": "希腊实行 2023 年至 2024 年推出的分级投资制度。该阈值取决于房产的位置和类型。",
    "Greece vs Dubai": "希腊 vs 迪拜",
    "Greece vs Portugal": "希腊 vs 葡萄牙",
    "Greece's Golden Visa sits at the intersection of all three. For €250,000, you don't just acquire a real estate asset in an EU country with one of the fastest-growing property markets in Europe. You acquire a foothold in the Mediterranean — one of the most liveable regions on earth — and EU residency that travels with your family.": "希腊的 Golden Visa 位于这三者的交汇处。用 250,000 欧元，您不仅仅是在 EU 国家（该国是欧洲房地产市场增长最快的国家之一）购买房地产资产。您在地中海（地球上最宜居的地区之一）获得了立足点，并获得了与家人一起旅行的 EU 居留权。",
    "Greece's Non-Dom Regime: How It Works": "希腊的非 Dom 政权：如何运作",
    "Greece's real estate legal framework is one of the most investor-protective in Southern Europe. Since 1990, foreign nationals have had full rights to purchase, own, and sell real estate anywhere in Greece (with minor restrictions near certain border zones). All transactions are notarised, title-registered, and electronically logged in the national cadastral system (Κτηματολόγιο).": "希腊的房地产法律框架是南欧最保护投资者的法律框架之一。自 1990 年以来，外国人拥有在希腊任何地方购买、拥有和出售房地产的充分权利（在某些边境地区有较小的限制）。所有交易均经过公证、产权登记并以电子方式记录在国家地籍系统 (Kτηματολόγιο) 中。",
    "Greece's residency program can unlock one of Europe's most competitive tax regimes: a €100,000 flat annual tax on global income, no wealth tax, and a capital gains framework designed for real estate investors.": "希腊的居留计划可以解锁欧洲最具竞争力的税收制度之一：每年10万欧元的全球收入统一税、无财富税以及专为房地产投资者设计的资本利得框架。",
