    "Important distinction: the non-dom regime requires becoming a Greek tax resident (183+ days/year). This is different from the Golden Visa, which requires no minimum stay. Investors interested in combining both must plan their residency structure carefully with qualified legal and tax counsel.": "重要区别：非 dom 制度要求成为希腊税务居民（每年 183 天以上）。这与 Golden Visa 不同，后者没有最短停留时间要求。有兴趣将两者结合的投资者必须与合格的法律和税务顾问仔细规划其居住结构。",
    "in Greece": "在希腊",
    "In Kolonaki — Athens' equivalent of Kensington or the 16th arrondissement — properties now trade at €4,000–€7,000/m². At these levels, an €800,000 investment secures a 120–200m² flagship apartment in the most sought-after residential address in Greece. The same capital in Paris, London, or Zurich buys 50–80m² in a comparable neighbourhood. The value differential is structural, not cyclical.": "在柯洛纳基（相当于雅典的肯辛顿区或第 16 区），房产现在的交易价格为每平方米 4,000 至 7,000 欧元。在这些水平上，800,000 欧元的投资可以在希腊最受欢迎的住宅地址购买一套 120-200 平方米的旗舰公寓。巴黎、伦敦或苏黎世的同一首都在类似的社区购买了 50-80 平方米的土地。价值差异是结构性的，而不是周期性的。",
    "In-depth articles on yields, tax, and strategy": "有关收益率、税收和策略的深入文章",
    "Inquire About This Property": "查询此房产",
    "Introduced in 2020 under Article 5A of the Greek Income Tax Code (Law 4172/2013), the non-domicile program targets high-net-worth individuals who transfer their tax residency to Greece. The mechanism is straightforward: pay a lump-sum €100,000 per year in lieu of any Greek income tax on foreign-sourced income. Business income, dividends, capital gains, rental income from overseas properties — all covered under the flat payment.": "非住所计划于 2020 年根据希腊所得税法（第 4172/2013 号法律）第 5A 条推出，针对将税务居民身份转移到希腊的高净值个人。该机制很简单：每年一次性支付 100,000 欧元，以代替希腊对外国收入征收所得税。业务收入、股息、资本利得、海外房产的租金收入——所有这些都包含在固定付款中。",
    "Investment Analysis — Greek Golden Visa": "投资分析 — 希腊语 Golden Visa",
